Reasoning: The paper deals with logical and topological tools for analyzing knowledge, knowability, and belief. The use of modal logic and topology suggests that the paper may belong to the Logic in Computer Science (cs.LO) sub-category. The paper also discusses the application of these tools to artificial intelligence, which suggests that it may also belong to the Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) sub-category. The use of topological subset spaces and the analysis of the structure of these spaces suggests that the paper may also belong to the Computational Complexity (cs.CC) and Mathematics (cs.MA) sub-categories. Finally, the paper's focus on providing sound and complete axiomatizations for the proposed logics suggests that it may also belong to the Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS) sub-category.
